The following error is a runtime error because we don't know how to catch those at compile-time:

  $ cat >div.asl <<EOF
  > func main () => integer
  > begin
  >   let x: integer = 5 DIV 3;
  >   return 0;
  > end
  > EOF

  $ aslref div.asl
  ASL Execution error: Illegal application of operator DIV for values 5 and 3.
  [1]

